### Chain 01 - Estimate-First NS Reformulation Cancellations

Central premise: if NS has a beyond-De-Giorgi escape in the spirit of SQG, it must show up as an estimate-level gain on a named localized interaction, not as a prettier identity. This chain tests only a short list of natural reformulations of the exact NS nonlinearity.

Why it belongs now: run-001 closed the remaining pressure-localization loophole, so the next cleanest live branch is the algebraic one that was already identified as the best reserve path.

### Chain 02 - Obstruction-First Geometry Route

Central premise: Tao averaging should destroy fine vortex geometry if geometry is truly the missing NS-specific ingredient. This chain separates local Beltrami deficit, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence instead of bundling them together.

Why it belongs now: it is still the strongest genuinely geometric branch, but it is now structured to attack the nonlocal stretching remainder early rather than drifting into descriptive vortex language.

### Chain 03 - Critical Element / Concentration-Compactness with NS-Specific Rigidity Screen

Central premise: if local estimate routes keep stalling, the right object may be a minimal blowup profile. This chain asks whether any currently available NS compactness package can be paired with a rigidity mechanism that is not already Tao-preserved.

Why it belongs now: it is the most globally different route in the landscape and has the highest proof ceiling, even though its floor is lower than Chains 01 and 02.

### Chain 04 - Strain-Pressure Eigenstructure

Central premise: the exact tensor identities linking strain, pressure Hessian, and vorticity stretching may encode NS-specific rigidity that is invisible at the level of scalar norm estimates. This chain tests that possibility at the eigenframe and sign-structure level.

Why it belongs now: it covers the tensorial middle ground between pure geometry and pure compactness without collapsing back into pressure-estimate relabeling.

## Major Differences Between Chains

- Chain 01 is algebraic and estimate-first. It succeeds only if a reformulation changes the operative localized interaction.
- Chain 02 is geometric and obstruction-first. It works on intense-vorticity observables and asks whether they control the full stretching mechanism.
- Chain 03 is global and dynamical. It assumes blowup and tries to isolate a minimal counterexample plus a rigidity lever.
- Chain 04 is tensorial. It focuses on eigenframes, sign structure, and exact strain-pressure identities rather than tube geometry or compactness.

## Portfolio Shape

- Highest floor: Chain 01 and Chain 02. Both can end with a sharp negative result that materially improves the mission map.
- Highest upside: Chain 03. If a genuine rigidity lever survives there, it changes the landscape.
- Best bridge branch: Chain 04. It can connect Tao's filter, vorticity geometry, and pressure structure without reopening the closed pressure-localization route.

## Selector Guidance

If the next execution run wants the best expected value, start with Chain 01.

If Chain 01 closes negatively, Chain 02 is the best next branch because it targets the strongest remaining NS-specific signal with a good failure payload.

If the next run wants maximum novelty ceiling instead of highest floor, Chain 03 is the deliberate gamble and Chain 04 is the disciplined bridge option.

